                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2930.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                            Juárez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juárez</hi> (<hi rend="italic">via El Paso,
                                Tex.</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ciudad Juárez peacefully surrendered to-day to General Campa with 800 men. Good
                    order prevails.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
